IMPORTANT:  Please note that this is NOT an actual interpretation of the song with ASL signs.  I decided to try something different so I interpreted the entire song using the letters of the alphabet A-Z (twice).  If you are familiar with Deaf culture then you are aware that ABC stories are highly valued and are often passed down throughout the community.   Enjoy!!

Thanks Wink for the awesome feedback!

media$description.$t:
I always use to just sing along to this song cause it has a great beat...but I finally realized what the song was about and appreciated it so much more.

I took a missions trip to the Dominican Republic and it was one of the most amazing experiences I've ever had.  To step vulnerably outside my little American bubble was one big slap of reality.  It opened my eyes to the world around me and forced me to realize that it's "not all about me!"

For those of you who don't know sign language... the main focus of this song is to bring to your attention the fact that the world is suffering.. but we're so consumed in our own problems and achievements that the only thing we can focus on is...ourselves
